  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: <span class=3DSpellE>Gravitic</sp=
an></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Biologically and physiologically, <span class=3DSpel=
lE>XHumans</span>
  are indistinguishable from Humans. This leads to confusion from other
  species, though Humans and <span class=3DSpellE>XHumans</span> insist on =
the
  division.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>XHuman</span> origins centered =
around an
  event known in Human history as the <span class=3DSpellE>Relakis</span> I=
ncident.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>During the <span class=3DSpellE>Shakturi</span> conf=
licts, Humanity
  desperately tried to develop whatever weapons they could to combat the
  extra-galactic invaders. This included bioweapons from the famed <span
  class=3DSpellE>Relakis</span> research institutes.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The &#8220;<span class=3DSpellE>Relakis</span> Incid=
ent&#8221;
  involved an accidental release of an intensely painful and virulent
  laboratory-grown disease. The disease was nearly 100% fatal, victims taki=
ng days
  to die in mind-shattering pain.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Relakis</span> was swiftly plac=
ed under
  quarantine and abandoned to its fate, as Humanity had to turn elsewhere i=
n their
  desperate fight against the <span class=3DSpellE>Shakturi</span>.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>After some generations, the few Human <span class=3D=
SpellE>Relakis</span>
  survivors began developing genetic immunity to the disease, though they s=
till
  carried genetic scars from exposure to it.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>So intense was the fear of a re-emergence of the <sp=
an
  class=3DSpellE>Relakis</span> disease that nearby Human colonies refused =
to
  consider re-opening <span class=3DSpellE>Relakis</span> to any Human cont=
act.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The few residents of <span class=3DSpellE>Relakis</s=
pan> who
  did travel through Human-controlled space were forced to register and wear
  encounter suits. They were shunned, turned away and branded &quot;Ex
  Humans&quot; as a slur.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Defiant, the 'Ex Humans' took up this moniker and us=
ed it
  to describe themselves as a new race entirely: the history of <span
  class=3DSpellE>XHumans</span> began.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>XHumans</span> culture differs =
from
  Human society in many ways. <span class=3DSpellE>XHumans</span> embrace
  cybernetic implantation, are much more collectivist and have no scruples
  about polyamory or group families. <span class=3DSpellE>XHumans</span> ha=
ve
  fewer inhibitions than Humans, seeing them as weak and indecisive.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>XHumans</span> and Humans find =
each
  other detestable. Something about the extreme familiarity, the very close=
 in
  looks but also noticeably different continues to make each race intoleran=
t of
  each other.</p>
